# Use this file to store your Password Pusher environment variables and pass to the
# Docker container.
#
# This can be passed to docker as:
# docker run -d --env-file ./pwpush-docker-env-file pglombardo/pwpush:latest
#
# This is not an authoratative list of possible environment variables.
# See the full list of supported configuration environment variables:
# https://docs.pwpush.com/docs/config-strategies/
# https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher/blob/master/config/settings.yml
#
# Docker syntax for this file is described here:
# https://docs.docker.com/compose/environment-variables/env-file/
